headline: CMS Energy (CMS) Announces Dividend for Series C Preferred Stock
summary: CMS Energy (CMS) recently declared a preferred dividend, reaffirming its commitment to shareholder value. Over the past month, CMS shares have risen by 7%, potentially reflecting investor confidence following strong Q2 earnings, which showed growth in sales and net income. During this period, CMS also confirmed a regular dividend with upcoming payment and record dates, adding to shareholder returns. Meanwhile, broader market indexes also gained, with the Nasdaq up significantly, suggesting...

headline: Alliant Energy Q2 Earnings Surpass Estimates, Revenues Miss
summary: LNT's second-quarter earnings improve 19.3% and beat estimates, but revenues miss despite year-over-year growth.
